
The javascript framework has the following folder structure:

common
libs
controllers
modules
templates

"common" stores the utility function that relates to the biz logic and can be re-used across the application
"lib" stores the api, data structure that doesnt tie to specific biz log. 
"controllers" stores the page level javascript codes
"modules" is a self-managed javascript widget which mange the template rendering, the UI or lib event handling, trigger
events destined to be listened outside of the module. 
"templates" stores the mustache templates.








